## Part 6: Optional — Set Up SSH Key for Passwordless Login

Skip this if you're fine entering your password each time. Otherwise:

**From PowerShell on your local machine:**

```powershell
# Generate a key (press Enter through the prompts to accept defaults)
ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "c95063223@rtx"

# Copy your public key to the bastion
type $env:USERPROFILE\.ssh\id_ed25519.pub | ssh xeta_jump "mkdir -p ~/.ssh && cat >> ~/.ssh/authorized_keys"

# Copy your public key to the target server
type $env:USERPROFILE\.ssh\id_ed25519.pub | ssh clara_copilot "mkdir -p ~/.ssh && cat >> ~/.ssh/authorized_keys"
```

After this, VS Code should connect without asking for a password.

